{"title":"Hover Text on MacOS","link":"https://twitter.com/Sommer/status/1355219192476127236","date":1611948042000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><section aria-labelledby=\"accessible-list-0\" role=\"region\"><h2 aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"auto\" role=\"heading\" id=\"accessible-list-0\">Conversation</h2><div aria-label=\"Timeline: Conversation\"><div><article role=\"article\" data-focusable=\"true\" tabindex=\"0\"><div><div data-testid=\"tweet\"><a href=\"https://twitter.com/Sommer\" role=\"link\" data-focusable=\"true\"><div aria-label=\"\"><p><img alt=\"\" draggable=\"true\" src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1332860357019267072/UUFspmgl_bigger.jpg\"></p></div></a></div><div><div><p><span>One of my fave Mac </span><span><a dir=\"ltr\" href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/accessibility?src=hashtag_click\" role=\"link\" data-focusable=\"true\">#accessibility</a></span><span> features: Hover Text. I have 2 displays; one is always harder for me to see, especially content to the far right. Hover Text is an awesome and super lightweight way to bring things into view! Find it in System Preferences -&gt; Accessibility -&gt; Zoom</span></p></div><div data-focusable=\"true\" tabindex=\"0\" data-testid=\"placementTracking\"><p><span>The media could not be played.</span></p></div></div></div></article></div><div><article role=\"article\" data-focusable=\"true\" tabindex=\"0\"><div data-testid=\"tweet\"><div><a href=\"https://twitter.com/wndxlori\" role=\"link\" data-focusable=\"true\"><div aria-label=\"\"><p><img alt=\"\" draggable=\"true\" src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1262890147114336256/cgpE_iA2_bigger.jpg\"></p></div></a></div><div><p><span>OMG. Thank you. I needed this so much, because I have continuing focus issues since my macular hole surgery.</span></p></div></div></article></div><div><article role=\"article\" data-focusable=\"true\" tabindex=\"0\"><div data-testid=\"tweet\"><div><a href=\"https://twitter.com/Sommer\" role=\"link\" data-focusable=\"true\"><div aria-label=\"\"><p><img alt=\"\" draggable=\"true\" src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1332860357019267072/UUFspmgl_bigger.jpg\"></p></div></a></div><div><p><span>So glad this will be useful to you!</span></p></div></div></article></div><div><article role=\"article\" data-focusable=\"true\" tabindex=\"0\"><div data-testid=\"tweet\"><div><a href=\"https://twitter.com/quephird\" role=\"link\" data-focusable=\"true\"><div aria-label=\"\"><p><img alt=\"\" draggable=\"true\" src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1346015608161255424/AELDsWrF_bigger.jpg\"></p></div></a></div><div><p><span>I never knew about this!!!</span></p></div></div></article></div><div><article role=\"article\" data-focusable=\"true\" tabindex=\"0\"><div data-testid=\"tweet\"><div><a href=\"https://twitter.com/stefan_3d\" role=\"link\" data-focusable=\"true\"><div aria-label=\"\"><p><img alt=\"\" draggable=\"true\" src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1344644842467581954/9zW68I1Y_bigger.jpg\"></p></div></a></div><div><p><span>What does a developer need to do to support this in custom UI? In my field, people rarely use Cocoa widgets and it would still be useful to have this feature.</span></p></div></div></article></div><div><article role=\"article\" data-focusable=\"true\" tabindex=\"0\"><div data-testid=\"tweet\"><div><a href=\"https://twitter.com/Sommer\" role=\"link\" data-focusable=\"true\"><div aria-label=\"\"><p><img alt=\"\" draggable=\"true\" src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1332860357019267072/UUFspmgl_bigger.jpg\"></p></div></a></div><div><p><span>As long as your views have an accessibility- label, frame, and role, it should work!</span></p></div></div></article></div></div></section></div>","author":"John Gruber","siteTitle":"Daring Fireball","siteHash":"fc569638025dadf22a867470f8215f38855cf50e975782a6c989909474292a36","entryHash":"eaf17d29a5353d36e216c6baca0c97a933f7c79e6d9d7525be959e2bb80ba5e3","category":"Tech"}